explanation:
Reasoning for each symbol (why required to decide if any code in OS_SocketBind is unreachable):

- OS_SocketBindAddress
  - The first call in OS_SocketBind. To decide whether the outer if (return_code == OS_SUCCESS) can ever be true (and thus whether the inner branches are reachable) you must know the possible return values and conditions of this function.

- OS_SocketBindAddress_Impl
  - The implementation called by OS_SocketBindAddress (per call graph). The actual logic that determines its return values may live here; needed to assess whether OS_SUCCESS can be produced.

- OS_SocketListen
  - The second call in OS_SocketBind. To determine whether the inner if (return_code == OS_ERR_INCORRECT_OBJ_TYPE) can ever be true you must know the possible return values and behavior of OS_SocketListen.

- OS_SocketListen_Impl
  - The implementation for OS_SocketListen where the real return-value decisions are made; required to see if OS_ERR_INCORRECT_OBJ_TYPE is a reachable return.

- OS_SUCCESS
  - Symbol (macro/enum constant) used in the conditional. Its value and semantics are required to evaluate the conditional comparisons and whether they can be satisfied by callee return values.

- OS_ERR_INCORRECT_OBJ_TYPE
  - Symbol tested in the inner conditional. Must know this value and the circumstances under which a callee can return it to determine reachability.

- UT_Stub_RegisterReturnType
  - Appears in the static call graph for the target path (unit-test/stub infrastructure). If the codebase uses the Unit Test stubs inside the socket functions to override return values, these stubs can make otherwise-unreachable branches reachable; their presence and behavior must be considered.

- UT_Stub_RegisterContextWithMetaData
  - Part of the unit-test stub registration chain shown in the call graph. Needed for the same reason as above: to understand whether test stubs can alter return values and thus affect reachability.

- UT_ExecuteBasicHandler
  - Part of the stub execution path. If OS_SocketListen/BindAddress delegate to the UT framework, this handler can return injected values; include it to determine possible return outcomes.

- UT_Stub_GetReturnValuePtr
  - Used by the UT stub framework to supply return values. Required to see if the framework can cause OS_SocketListen/BindAddress to return OS_ERR_INCORRECT_OBJ_TYPE or OS_SUCCESS.

- UT_GetStubEntry / UT_DefaultStubImpl
  - Representative core UT helpers (appearing in the call graph of the UT helpers). Included so the analyzer can trace how the UT framework chooses/returns stubbed values (affects reachability analysis).

Note: The minimal essential symbols to check reachability are the two callees (OS_SocketBindAddress, OS_SocketListen) and the constants tested (OS_SUCCESS, OS_ERR_INCORRECT_OBJ_TYPE). The additional Impl and UT stub symbols are required if those functions delegate behavior into implementation files or unit-test stub machinery that can change possible return values; include them if you need a complete, sound determination of whether any branch in OS_SocketBind is unreachable.
